JSTL (Java pages Standard Tag Library) Notes
1. JSTL are a set of predefined tags from Oracle
2. There are many tags used but the most used are the core tags (c:, ex- c:if, c:for)
3. JSTL allows you to write out a lot of programming logic without using Java


To use JSTL tags, you must copy jstl.jar and standard.jar inTO your WEB-INF lib folder

Evaluates an expression then prints to the screen
<c:out value="{10+9}" 

Assigns value and scope to a variable
-scope can be application, request, session or context
<c:set var="score" scope="session" value="${80}"> 

Removes a variable from a scope
<c:remove var="score"> 

Using if conditional 
<c: if>
	//code here
</c:if>


//Similar to Java switch statement
<c:choose>

//Looping statement
<c:forEach>